column5: always like the steelhead and float rod pics but havent got on yet bc i just started but if u got any please show  once i get on im def. posting it
BillM->Frogwater reel? Thrilla->Can't tell...Loomis reel (totally wild guess)?  Nice pics!
Do fly reels count?       Ok, fine!  Have a pin
Nice pix! What kind of rod is in the 2nd pic? Nice reels too! Is the first one an Amundson? It looks similar to mine, but it's orange. The second one a Lamson?

First combo is Sage, 9' 8 wt VT-2 paired with 3880 CF.  Second is Amundson, 12' 7-8wt paired with Trend 9/10.  Ps. I love the fact that someone recognized the Amundson as this is one of my favourite "lesser known" fly companies.

Oh crap. lol I just jumped onto Amundon's website and is that your photo on the front page? If so, nicely done.  I thought the first pic was the Amundson reel. lol It kinda looks like my TCR reel, but in orange. I'm more than happy with it. It's a great company, despite only have the reel for a month.

Haha, yep that's mine.  I took that pic while fishing with Amundson's Ontario rep (who is also a member on OFC) and he asked he could use it as a promo.  Never tried the TCR's but I've used a WW Feather Lite and was very pleased.  For the price, it has a great drag and is very light.
First pic's a huge Erie hen from a few years ago ,second is a nice buck and was playin around with camera angles with the waterproof fuji.
And the raven sang... caw!  recovered dropback male   beat up chunky hen   droppie hen really close to home   shiny new huron male   well fed wild lake O. hen   ad nauseum...  p.-
